		<hr size="1">Woh someone needs a hug...</P><P>I have posted quite a bit recently on this subject, and I agree that bringing the need for melee balancing to SOE's attention is very important!  Without going into the many things I've already said in other posts, the basic point is that the Warrior needs to be the BEST of the melee classes, much like the Cleric is the BEST of the healer classes.  There needs to be more distinction to the Warrior to raise her above Paladins, SKs and Rangers who can and often do perform better than a warrior.  </P><P>I'm not saying that all warrior's problems will be cured by this, there will still be idiots running around with stupid gear selections who have no idea how to play the Warr effectively.  This is not for those people.  This is for those of us who are serious about our Warr char and wish to see some improvement to this class.</P><P>Anyways, I for one will participate in the Stand Down, and I will be sure to pass word along to my guild and server.  who knows? Can't hurt to try...</P><P>Sriani HeartofWolf<BR>Warrior - RZ<BR>Dissonant Intervention (Leader)<BR>Group: "Can you please pull faster?" <BR>Warrior: *kills group, makes off with loot*<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
