		<hr size="1">Let me start off my rant by saying that a Warrior is my most favorite class to group with (I'm a Rogue).</P><P>Having said that...whats your beef???!!!!!</P><P>Warriors ARE the best melee class...AT TAKING DAMAGE!!!</P><P>Thats your job!  DAMAGE MITIGATION.  Taking a beating so your group doesn't.  </P><P>Why do you feel you have to have the best damage output also?  You are plenty powerfull as is.</P><P>Are you saying you should be able to outdamage a Rogue of equal level?  You do realize that the Rogue wouldn't be able to do that kind of damage without (YOU) the warriors, taunting and taking the damage for them?</P><P>Do you realize that at level 52 my Rogue has 2k hps, and many of my buddies Warriors at the same level have 3.5k or more?  </P><P>So your complaint is: you want to do the most damage AND have the most hitpoints AND the best damage mitigation???  </P><P>Thats stupid.  It would unbalance the game so bad its not even funny.</P><P>People need to understand: every class has its claim to fame.  Every class has its role.  The Warrior class is by far the best at what it was designed to do: take damage while dealing a decent amount of melee output.  So you don't do as much physical damage as some other classes.  Deal with it!!!!!</P><P>Now maybe I've gotten the wrong impression of what is desired by the Warriors who feel like they are getting the short end of the stick?  Am I missing something?  Is your beef not melee related at all but possibly Taunt/Hate, Skill/Disc related?</P><P>Please enlighten us, as the above posts have been laughably vague as to what the actual complaint is.</P><P><BR>Message edited by: Silvaira (11/10/2003 10:16:21 PM)<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
