		<hr size="1">Listen, don't shoot the messenger.  I brought this here to discuss amongst you to see what your opinions would be on the subject.  You are entitled to them and I also respect what you say.  Although you may have misunderstood me.</P><P><i>Not a major change, mind you, but one that will make warriors a much happier class.</i></P><P>This is what I said.  A warrior's role is to stand in front of the mob and take the damage.  Period.  I am serious about protecting my casters when grouped and I do consider myself a good tank.  Pre-level 51 I had a harder time gaining aggro, post-51 it's gotten easier.  However, there's always the occasional Rouge's bs, wizard's nuke, or Cleric's CH that sends the mob scurrying on over to take a few whacks.  This becomes aggravating to me, because that means I've failed my role and didn't maintain aggro.  Albeit, it's only briefly, but still.  Going back to what I said, a minor change would be nice and there are several ideas I've seen tossed around.  Good ideas such as giving us a higher % taunt that will enrage the mob to us more than any other class or possibly giving all warriors a stun-like ability that keeps him on us.  Something like that.  No where did I say, "I want to outdamage Rouges!"  That's just unrealistic.</P><P>As for being vague, that was done on purpose.  I wanted you to click the link, read up a little, and maybe see the other reactions from other warriors and try to understand our viewpoint instead of blurting out, "Stop whining."  I do not whine.  I play the game to have fun and that's it.  However, it becomes aggravating to be passed over for a Paladin and/or an SK, while LFG, because they can hold aggro better due to the spells they have to help them.  Believe you me, I don't want spells.  I want to take a beating.  If you really want to engage a conversation to get other opinions, please feel free to post on that Steel Warrior mb.</P><P>As some of you are probably aware a tank is only as good as his/her armor/weapons.  Beings that my warrior is my main, gathering pp isn't as easy as I would like.  With me being a casual player, I find the higher I get in level the more I'm outgrowing my armor.  I do not feel comfortable asking people for pp or armor, whether they're guildies or not...just not my style.  <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/smile.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle><BR><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
