		<hr size="1">Well, as I have stated in other posts, I am not looking for a warrior who can heal/rez/dot/nuke or any of that stuff, we are used to living without those things by now.  A warrior isn't a caster. End of story.</P><P>What we are looking for is a better taunt that will get better/longer/etc. as we lvl, allowing us to hold/keep aggro with more surety. I for one would be much impressed and satisfied to gain some skills for my class, such as a "first aid" skill perhaps? Someone in another thread mentioned that warriors should be most skilled at "field medics" - perhaps we could get a faster/better bandage skill, the ability to bandage self only to 70%? </P><P>Also, some attack skills would be awesome - maybe something along the lines of a 30 second self haste that improves in % as we lvl? Not a "buff" per say or a magic of any sort, jsut a clickable skill like taunt ..? Also the berserker skill could be much improved on!  It should be a clicky effect also, with a certain time limit that grows with lvl.</P><P>Anywayz, I'm not sure exactly what the Warrior StandDown people want, but those are my ideas and the ideas of others that I have seen in other threads. Perhaps instead of just a random vague message, we should /petition ACTUAL IDEAS! Least, that's what I'll do...</P><P>Much love to my melee buddies, I for one would much rather have a group that INCLUDES a rogue, pally or sk than be alone =(  Tanking alone is just a suicide ticket, and this warrior is NOT asking to have that ability!</P><P></P><P>Sriani HeartofWolf<BR>Warrior - RZ<BR>Dissonant Intervention (Leader)<BR>"I'm not a ranger."<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
