		<hr size="1">Well at least the discussion turned towards some suggestions/ideas.</P><P>Don't petition them in game however, but DO /feedback them in game.  The more people that do this the better.</P><P>I do not have a lot of experience playing a War (only played one till lvl 34) but as a lvl 50 Wizzie I do group with War's often.</P><P>While I think giving them a better taunt, i.e. an additional taunt skill like 'enrage mob' with a timer (as has been already suggested) is a good idea it needs to be kept minor.  Why do I say this?  Given a War's high AC and HP pool if a War could grab agro and keep it hands down it would be unbalancing.  Team such a super taunting War with a Clerc to complete heal and you have a receipe for a boring group.  No one else in the group would have to think.  Cleric could heal without thougth of timing, Wiz's could nuke till blue in the face, Rogues BS as fast as they could hit the button, etc.  Where is the strategy?  I agree with other posters, it is the entire groups responsibility to aid the War in keeping agro.  It is NOT the failure of the War is a Wiz nukes early and gets agro.  I'd also add that it is okay if a SK or Ranger can grab agro better, they pay a price, once they have it they get beat down fast...</P><P>So maybe a better taunt is not the answer for a War, perhaps a small 'tweak' in their HP so it is that much more than the other classes.  Even if they cannot taunt any better, it will become clear to a well working group that it is to their advantage to help the War keep agro by using a little strategy.  That is the case now but a little more HP would carve out their nitch a little deeper.</P><P>Azzara (lvl 50 Wiz on Drinal)</P><P><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
