		<hr size="1">Actually this "Stand down" isn't about complaining that warriors need changing.</P><P>Because SOE <i>already acknowledge</i> that warriors, in fact all the pure melee classes, need some changes. In fact, the EQLive future news section has included the following statement since at least May 2003:</P><P><i>5) Class Balance </P><P>We're still planning to take a look at improving the damage capabilities of melee classes, as they've fallen behind their magic-using counterparts at the very high end of the game. Finding the proper solutions for this situation will take some time. Some options being considered are:</P><P>Improve melee damage-increasing disciplines <BR>Improve Planes of Power melee weapons </i></P><P>That statement has been included, unchanged, in the "Future plans" section on EQLive every month since May 2003 (could even be earlier, not bothered checking) and each month, it's just repeated without any further change or comment from SOE.</P><P>All the warriors are asking for from the "Stand down" is an updated statement from SOE on what they actually plan to <b>do</b> with melee balancing. If you read the thread linked, you'll see that the basic plea that this "Stand down" is making, which is included in the the AFK message that everyone is asked to use, is:</P><P>"I demand a statement be issued concerning Melee balancing."</P><P>That's all they want - just an update on what SOE are actually planning to do, as SOE have been saying for months that they're going to do something but have never actually come out and actually said what.</P><P><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
