		<hr size="1">Yea I got a little riled up...I guess mostly because people don't know how to elaborate, and make thier points clear.</P><P>I was responding to the following from Sriani HeartofWolf:<BR>"Without going into the many things I've already said in other posts, the basic point is that the Warrior needs to be the BEST of the melee classes, much like the Cleric is the BEST of the healer classes. There needs to be more distinction to the Warrior to raise her above Paladins, SKs and Rangers who can and often do perform better than a warrior."</P><P>This statement basically made me think that you guys wanted warriors to be the best melee damage class...which would not be a good thing.</P><P>Taunt?  Aggro management?  Yes, you should be the best at that.  However, should you be so good at it that you never lose it?  No.  Casters shouldn't be able to nuke without fear of getting a little aggro, Clerics shouldn't be amune from getting whacked a few times after a Cheal, Rogues should get some attention if they get off a few choice backstabs...you get the idea.  This is the way the game has pretty much always worked.  Nobody should be able to hold aggro under all circumstances...it takes away the risk for the other players...and there should be risk, or why play?</P><P><BR>Message edited by: Silvaira (11/11/2003 9:16:33 PM)<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
