		<hr size="1">What level of the game are you talking about?  At the mid-50's warriors are still desired by most of my raids and groups.  True a pally and sk can tank too, but they need more attention and mana from the healers to do it.</P><P>Lots of classes can pull plenty good.  Haven't heard of anyone shunning a particular class because they couildn't pull.</P><P>Casters outdamaging Rogues?  Short term maybe, but rogues can backstag once every 7 ticks, all day long.  In the long run, they still put out the most damage.  Plus, they are great for traps and locks in LDoN.</P><P>I dissagree that melee's have no place in EQ.  Have casters and hybrids been given extra attention lately?  Yes they have.  And if you remember your EQ history, hybrids were complaining about EXACTLY the same things you just mentioned..."nobody needs us"..."nobody wants us"..."others can do what we can"...etc...etc...</P><P>What had to be done is something subtle.  Just enough tweaking to bring the melees up slightly...otherwise you'll be right back in the same boat.  EQ can't get into the ever escalating problem of having to bump one class up every time them bump someone elses class up.  There would be no end to it.  There has to be a point when everyone steps back and says "yep, I'm good with the way the classes are now".</P><P>I think we should cut the guys at Sony some slack because we are the ones that demand new content, and items, and spells, and skills, and encounters, and all this stuff...just to keep the game fresh and interesting so that we want to keep playing.  Mainting balance while catering to our demands has got to be a tough thing.</P><P>And by the way, you could have complete and total balance...and some people will still scream bloody murder...because some people are just never satisfied with a level playing field.  They must be the uber'est!<BR><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
